name: Highway Hotel
street: Corner Forrest Ave and Spencer Street
directions: Enter through main door of hotel; the toilets are well signposted.
comment: Available opening hours of hotel, usually 11am-midnight or later.  Designated accessible parking.  Main entrance has steps and ramp.  Manual door to toilet.

name: Bunbury Plaza
directions: Can also be accessed via Spencer Street.  The toilets are along the strip of buildings near the butcher's shop, rather than inside the centre proper.
comment: Available during centre opening hours (7am-9pm).  Designated accessible parking, but not terribly near the toilets.  Manual doors.

name: The Village Arcade
comment: Available during opening hours of the Arcade.  Gendered multi-stall toilets, non-gendered/accessible stall with change facilities and sharps disposal.  Electric door.  Designated accessible parking undercover.  Ample free street and undercover parking.

name: McHenry Hohnen Cellar Door
comment: Open business hours.  Change table only available in stall marked "women".  Designated accessible parking, with paved parking area and ramp to cellar door.  Stalls have manual doors.  There is a patio with tables, also picnic tables and a nice grass area accessed by a steep grass slope from the car park.

name: Margaret River Venison
directions: The toilet is not marked; it's the door to the left as you approach the entrance.
comment: Available 9-5.  No designated accessible parking.  Car park is firm gravel.  There is a ramp to the shop and toilet, but one step into both.

name: Olio Bello
directions: Turn down Armstrong Road from Cowaramup Beach Road.  Once parked, the toilet is under the verandah around the corner of the building.
comment: Available 10-4.  Has designated accessible parking which is paved; the main lot is gravel.  The toilet is outside and you don't have to pass workers to use it.  It's stocked with lovely supplies, including hand creams, gloves and wipes with the change table.  Great coffee.

name: Lefthanders Beach
directions: From Caves Road, turn west into Cowaramup Bay Road.  This turns into Bayview Drive, then Salter Street.  Follow the road up the hill.  Turn right onto the gravel road, just before the main road becomes gravel.  Take the first right to get close to the toilets, or drive straight ahead and park in the carpark.
comment: Difficult accessibility for independent people with mobility issues.  There is a paved path to the toilet block, but there are no rails in the stall and the doors have an awkward latch.  They are plenty wide enough to accommodate a wheelchair, though.  No designated accessible parking.  Like many toilets in the Leeuwin-Naturaliste National Park, this is a composting toilet and has no water or handwashing facilities.  There is beach access by multiple stairs.

name: Cowaramup Bay car park
directions: Turn west off Caves Road into Cowaramup Bay Road.  This becomes Bayview Drive.  The carpark is on your right, at the bottom of the steep hill.
comment: The carpark is gravel and sand.  There is an assigned Accessible carpark, but it's quite rough and wheelchair users may find it difficult.  There is a good path to the toilet block.  The doors are manual.  24 hour access, but no lights.  No drinking water available.  Beach access.

name: Crystal
directions: Text (562) 245-9275 any time day or night to confirm availability. If no response in 5 minutes, assume unavailable
comment: This is a private residence, no changing table but you may bring children here to change them.
